#: ../../source/help/settings/account-settings.rst:185
msgid "Teammate Name Display"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/settings/account-settings.rst:187
msgid ""
"Configure how names are displayed in the user interface: nickname, "
"username or full name. The default for this setting is dependent on the "
"`configuration set by the System Admin "
"<https://docs.mattermost.com/administration/config-settings.html"
"#teammate-name-display>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/settings/account-settings.rst:190
msgid "Timezone"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/settings/account-settings.rst:192
msgid ""
"Select the timezone used for timestamps in the user interface and email "
"notifications. The setting `must first be enabled by the System Admin "
"<https://docs.mattermost.com/administration/config-"
"settings.html#timezone>`__ by replacing ``false`` with ``true`` in "
"config.json."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/settings/account-settings.rst:195
msgid "Website Link Previews"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/settings/account-settings.rst:197
msgid ""
"When available, the first web link in a message will show a preview of "
"the website content below the message. This `setting must be enabled by "
"your System Admin <https://docs.mattermost.com/administration/config-"
"settings.html#link-previews>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/settings/account-settings.rst:200
msgid "Link Previews"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/settings/account-settings.rst:202
msgid ""
"Select whether links posted in Mattermost show a preview below them. When"
" \"On\", a preview will be shown below links to Youtube Videos and GIF, "
"PNG, JPEG, and BMP files. When \"Off\", no preview will be shown. This "
"setting can also be controlled using the slash commands ``/expand`` and "
"``/collapse``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/settings/account-settings.rst:205
msgid "Message Display"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/settings/account-settings.rst:207
msgid ""
"Select the formatting for messages in the center channel. \"Compact\" "
"mode decreases the spacing around posts, collapses link previews, and "
